# ── How env vars work in this project ────────────────────────────────────────
# Secrets are stored in AWS Secrets Manager (startline/{env}/app) and loaded
# automatically via .envrc + direnv when you cd into any worktree:
#
#   1. Install direnv (brew install direnv) and hook it into your shell
#   2. Run direnv allow in each worktree (one-time)
#   3. Ensure AWS CLI credentials are configured (the pool-ID lookup works)
#
# The .envrc file at the repo root handles everything. No .env file needed.
#
# ── Local-only constants ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# These are hardcoded in .envrc because they never change per machine.
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/startline?schema=public"
SMTP_HOST="localhost"
SMTP_PORT="1025"
